          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Magic Medicine</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.38)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23760">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9749">Matt "MrTopdeck" Loomis</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9749&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Free Mist Hyrens, and massive card drawing, who could ask for more?</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> June 4, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Eryss<br>
(Starting: Gremble, Fog Hyren, Poison <a href="javascript:card_browser(501)">Baloo Root</a>, N&#39;kala)<br>
<br>
Emlob<br>
(Starting: Mist Hyren)<br>
<br>
Yog<br>
(Starting: Yog&#39;s Maul)<br>
<br>
Creatures (27)<br>
Moob x3<br>
Trulb x3<br>
Zungg x3<br>
Treepsh x3<br>
Slarnath x3<br>
Flame Trulb x3<br>
Fog Hyren x3<br>
Mist Hyren x3<br>
Poison <a href="javascript:card_browser(501)">Baloo Root</a> x1<br>
N&#39;Kala x1<br>
Gremble x1<br>
<br>
Relics (11)<br>
Deadwood Staff x3<br>
Bog Stone x2<br>
Yog&#39;s Maul x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(734)">Climbing Staff</a> x2<br>
Inhibitor Band x2<br>
<br>
Spells (2):<br>
Sandswirl x2<br>
<br>
Total: 40 Cards<br>
<br>
Deck Design by Matt Loomis<br>
Design modified and tested by Matt Loomis and Bart Robinson   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck is simply put, a machine.<br>
<br>
The first magi is there simply for her abilty to end the turn with 7 new cards in your hand, as well as have spent out most of her energy, and have three creatures left on the board.  It&#39;s even better if she lives past the first turn, giving you the chance to use the Fog Hyren more than once, as well as play and use any Treepsh or Slarnath you draw to cycle through the deck even more.  Try not to play too much under Eryss, but don&#39;t hold back everything either.  You need to decide what&#39;s important to keep for the next magi, and what you can afford to sacrifice to buy time to draw a few more cards.  Her effect is almost never used, but it does prevent an Ormagon that&#39;s not coming out of Underneath.  I&#39;ve choosen her as a starting Magi over Baa because I&#39;ve had Eryss live past the first turn, whereas Baa almost never did.<br>
<br>
Emlob is the real key to the deck, using his effect of Imaginary Friends to the fullest advantage, you are able to maximize the potential of Mist Hyren, Moob, Trulb, and of course, Deadwood Staff.<br>
<br>
The Staff is where some real power comes in, allowing a double reduction on the Mist Hyren, making them cost 1 energy if you have 3 non-imaginary friends in play.  With any luck of your draw, the rest of your game will be played out on Emlob.  You&#39;ve got massive drawing power with the Fog Hyren, Treepsh, and Slarnaths, as well as recursion in the deck using the Bog Stone.  Most often, you&#39;ll be fetching back a Moob every turn, to gain upwards of ten energy with a typical swarm.  Otherwise the key choices are Fog Hyren to refill the hand, or Mist Hyren for the insane energy gain.<br>
<br>
As for the last Magi, he&#39;s there as a finisher, if you manage to get to him, you&#39;ll take their largest creature, attack them with it, and then play out whatever you&#39;ve got in your hand, sacrificing another weenie to the Yog&#39;s Maul to kill something else if it&#39;s still necessary.<br>
<br>
The Zunggs and the Flame Trulbs are for a little bit of added control with the Yog&#39;s Maul, which is yet another energy gain with both your swarm, and the Imaginary Friends effect.  <br>
<br>
The deck has already been highly metagamed, with the Sandswirls, Climbing Staffs, and Imhibitor Bands.  All of which are very useful in the right situations.  Namely the ones that you&#39;d rather not find yourself in, but always seems to anyway.  The two relics are almost necessary when trying to win on one Magi, because you need to prevent things like Bloom/Ninx, or Ormagon/Impact.  As well as preventing Rayje&#39;s Belts and Warrior&#39;s Boots from your opponent, two cards that this deck just doesn&#39;t need to play.  The Sandswirls are multi-purpose, allowing you to get past Burrow, and if you manage to topdeck it in time, Reef Hyrens.<br>
<br>
The biggest weakness to the deck is going second to an opening Reef Hyren, in which case I would just grab a Fog Hyren for the starting, and hope for the Sandswirl. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23760"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23760" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
